name: ray
description: Ray provides a simple, universal API for building distributed applications.

repo_metadata.description: Ray is a unified framework for scaling AI and Python applications. Ray consists of a core distributed runtime and a set of AI Libraries for accelerating ML workloads.

advisories.title: Ray OS Command Injection vulnerability
advisories.description: A command injection exists in Ray's cpu_profile URL parameter allowing attackers to execute os commands on the system running the ray dashboard remotely without authentication.

advisories.title: Ray Path Traversal vulnerability
advisories.description: LFI in Ray's log API endpoint allows attackers to read any file on the server without authentication. The issue is fixed in version 2.8.1+. Ray maintainers response can be found here: https://www.anyscale.com/blog/update-on-ray-cves-cve-2023-6019-cve-2023-6020-cve-2023-6021-cve-2023-48022-cve-2023-48023

advisories.title: Ray Missing Authorization vulnerability
advisories.description: LFI in Ray's /static/ directory allows attackers to read any file on the server without authentication. The issue is fixed in version 2.8.1+. Ray maintainers response can be found here: https://www.anyscale.com/blog/update-on-ray-cves-cve-2023-6019-cve-2023-6020-cve-2023-6021-cve-2023-48022-cve-2023-48023
